remarks: Equivalence of two versions of the Axiom of Choice ~ ax-ac .  The proof uses neither AC nor the Axiom of Regularity.  The right-hand side expresses our AC with the fewest number of different variables. (Contributed by NM, 5-Apr-2004.)
statement:
aceq1 $p |- ( E. y A. z e. x A. w e. z E! v e. z E. u e. y ( z e. u /\ v e. u ) <-> E. y A. z A. w ( ( z e. w /\ w e. x ) -> E. x A. z ( E. x ( ( z e. w /\ w e. x ) /\ ( z e. x /\ x e. y ) ) <-> z = x ) ) ) $.
$d u v w x y z $.
